Cico Privacy Policy

Effective: May 12, 2026

Cico is a plant-based food community platform for sharing recipes, logging craft batches, and trading ingredients. This policy explains in plain language what data we handle, why, and how you can control it.

1. Who We Are
Cico is operated from California, United States. Questions about privacy can be sent to: ricardoalvarezlda@gmail.com

2. Data We Collect

a) Account data — email address (or Apple ID token if you use Sign in with Apple), chosen username, and optional profile photo. We do not store raw Apple credentials.

b) Content you create — recipes, batch journal entries, ingredient trade listings, and comments you choose to post publicly. This content is stored on-device and synced to Cico servers only when you tap "Share."

c) Usage signals — which screens you visit, features you tap, and approximate session length. We collect this in aggregate to improve the app; it is not tied to advertising profiles.

d) Purchase receipts — when you subscribe or send a Treat, Apple forwards a transaction receipt to our servers for entitlement verification. We do not receive your payment card details.

e) Device metadata — iOS version, device model, crash logs. Used solely for stability improvements.

3. How We Use Your Data
We use the data above to: run and improve the Cico platform; verify your subscription entitlements; show your public recipes and journal highlights to other members; respond to support requests; and comply with law.

We do not sell your personal data. We do not use your recipe or batch content to train AI models.

4. Third-Party Services
We use Apple StoreKit 2 for in-app purchases and AppsFlyer for install attribution. AppsFlyer receives an anonymised device identifier and install event; it does not receive your recipes or journal content. You may opt out of AppsFlyer tracking via iOS Settings → Privacy → Tracking.

5. Content You Share
Recipes, listings, and comments you post publicly are visible to all Cico members. You retain ownership of your content. By making content public you grant Cico a limited, non-exclusive licence to display it within the platform. You can delete your public content at any time from your profile.

6. Data Retention
We keep your account data while your account is active. If you delete your account, we remove your personal data within 30 days, except where retention is required by law. On-device data (batch journals, custom inventory) is deleted when you uninstall the app.

7. Children
Cico is not intended for users under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe a child has created an account, please contact us and we will remove it promptly.

8. Your Rights
Depending on your location you may have the right to access, correct, export, or delete your personal data. To exercise these rights, email us at ricardoalvarezlda@gmail.com. We will respond within 30 days.

9. Security
We use TLS for data in transit and AES-256 encryption for data at rest. No system is perfectly secure; please use a strong, unique password and enable two-factor authentication where available.

10. Updates
We may update this policy when our practices change. We will post the revised policy in-app with an updated effective date. Continued use of Cico after an update constitutes acceptance.

